news.title: Financial relief for owners without lease deeds in Jaipur
news.para: Decision has been taken to exempt fines and interest imposed on regularisation charges on owners who do not have lease deeds (patta) of their plots/houses.

news.title: Rajasthan: Relief for residents who failed to carry out construction on purchased plots
news.para: An official said people who purchase plots through auction or lottery have to carry out minimum construction in the vacant plot in a stipulated time.

news.title: Construction sites not using dust screens under Nashik civic body scanner
news.para: In January last year, the NMC had made use of dust screens mandatory for construction sites in order to curb air pollution in the city. Initially, the dust screens were used by the builders at construction sites, but gradually a section of builders allegedly started violating the rule.

news.title: IIFL Housing Finance looks at co-lending model to grow
news.para: The housing finance company, which has a loan book that is around 46% of IIFL’s loans, has developed expertise in lending for affordable housing, which now serves as a competitive advantage.

news.title: Infosys co-founder buys two properties for Rs 76 crore in Bengaluru
news.para: Gopalkrishnan, now chairman of Axilor Ventures, which invests in early stage startups, bought the two properties in Koramangala 3rd Block.

news.title: YEIDA to launch housing plot scheme near Jewar airport site soon
news.para: Officials have been told to locate about 1,000 feasible plots ranging from 120 to 300 sqm in these two sectors. GNIDA is also preparing to launch a built-up residential housing scheme in sectors Xu 1, 2 and 3 by the middle of this month.

news.title: Sebi moves SC against SAT order on PNB Housing's Rs 4,000 crore preference issue
news.para: SAT directed that its interim order of June 21, 2021 will continue till further orders, restraining PNB Housing Finance from disclosing the voting results by the shareholders on the fund raise plan.

news.title: Embassy REIT to raise up to Rs 300 crore via debentures
news.para: In a regulatory filing, the company informed that the board of Embassy Office Parks Management Services Pvt Ltd, the manager to Embassy Office Parks REIT, had in November last year approved the raising of debt, including the issue of non-convertible debentures, for an aggregate amount up to Rs 3,641.1 crore in one or more tranches.

news.title: PMC bank scam: ED attaches HDIL group's shares worth Rs 233 crore
news.para: The ED said that HDIL has the right for the allotment of under-construction flats measuring 90,250 square feet Floor Space Index (FSI) in Ghatkopar, Mumbai of the developer Aryaman Developers Private Limited.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh forms SIT to identify colluding Noida officials in Supertech case
news.para: "Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath has directed to form an SIT at the government level immediately for investigation in Noida's twin towers case. Instructions were given to fix the accountability of officers of the authority who were associated with this case from 2004 to 2017," said the Chief Minister's office on Thursday.

news.title: NCDRC orders Supertech's managing director to be present at each hearing
news.para: The direction came after Arora appeared before the Commission only in response to bailable warrants issued against him in April this year in connection with failure to give possession to joint buyers of a villa in Sector 17A of Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Area despite a long delay.

news.title: To stop Mumbai from sinking, government to set up CM-led panel on climate change
news.para: Calling for mitigating measures, the environment department, while making the presentation, reiterated that if temperatures rise by 2-2.5 degrees Celsius on account of climate change, the city and the state will be among the world’s worst-affected spots.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body's property tax collection rises 9% in April-Aug 2021
news.para: All eight zones have registered a rise. Yelahanka zone (24 per cent) saw the highest jump, while Mahadevapura (3 per cent) the lowest.

news.title: Walton Street BlackSoil Real Estate Debt Fund II raises Rs 360 crore
news.para: The fund, which has an additional green-shoe option of Rs 250 crore, plans to invest the generated funds into self-liquidating senior secured debt instruments, focusing on middle-income residential real estate projects across key tier I cities of Bangalore, Hyderabad, Chennai, Mumbai, Pune and Delhi-NCR.

news.title: Karnataka HC backs property buyer, says judge shouldn't be swayed by protest plea
news.para: Complainant BP Manjunath had challenged the police’s ‘B’ report by filing the protest petition, claiming purchaser CH Nagaraja Rao of Mysuru issued a life threat to him in November 2009 over his auctioned property.
